Context Modern hiring tools mostly act as tracking systems rather than intelligent assistants.
Recruiters still spend significant time screening resumes, shortlisting candidates, scheduling
interviews, and assessing candidate fit.
Problem Statement Build an AI-powered hiring platform that augments recruiter decision-making
by automatically analyzing candidate data, ranking applicants, and streamlining the hiring
workflow.
AI Capabilities to Explore
Resume parsing and semantic skill extraction
Candidate-job fit scoring using embeddings
AI-generated candidate summaries and interview questions
Automatic screening and shortlist recommendations
Conversational assistant for recruiters to query candidate pipelines
Bias detection or explainable scoring
Possible Features
Upload job description → AI generates screening criteria
Resume ingestion → structured candidate profiles
AI shortlist suggestions with reasoning
Recruiter chat interface: “Show top backend engineers with Kubernetes experience”
AI-generated interview kits
Expected Outcome A prototype ATS with embedded AI agents that reduces recruiter effort and
improves candidate discovery